            <abstract id="ref2" label="Abstract">The letters are mainly between Burton Chance and Samuel Wood, a librarian at the Royal College of Surgeons of England who conducted bibliographic work for Chance. They concern the history of ophthalmology, with reference to Sir William Bowman, Joseph Lister, and John Milton's vision problems, among other information that Wood supplied Chance. There are also letters from Karl and Frederick Weinberger concerning personal matters.</abstract>
